1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

4
00:00:15,130 --> 00:00:17,650
I was really happy when we
joined the company at the same time.

5
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:26,940
That's why...

6
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:31,760
I never want to let you go again.

7
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:39,350
Zen, to me...

8
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:46,120
you've always been someone special.

9
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:07,400
"Fake Fact Lips"

10
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:12,500
(Episode 4: Are You a Demon?!)

11
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:26,380
Shido-san?

12
00:02:27,110 --> 00:02:28,110
Whoa!

13
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:29,580
Is everything okay?

14
00:02:30,830 --> 00:02:31,560
Huh?

15
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,490
What do you mean?

16
00:02:32,510 --> 00:02:34,260
Your desk is a total mess.

17
00:02:34,620 --> 00:02:36,060
I've never seen it like this before.

18
00:02:36,910 --> 00:02:38,510
I was just about to clean it up.

19
00:02:48,110 --> 00:02:49,110
So cold!

20
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:50,760
Good work today.

21
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:02,940
Zen, to me...

22
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,740
you've always been someone special.

23
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,100
Sorry.

24
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,090
I think I'll head home first.

25
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:33,150
Huh?

26
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:39,330
What the hell...

27
00:03:41,290 --> 00:03:42,390
Shido-san.

28
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,950
Shido-san?

29
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:46,900
Yeah?

30
00:03:47,370 --> 00:03:48,730
You dropped something.

31
00:03:49,570 --> 00:03:50,570
What?

32
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,119
Don't be silly, I didn't drop anything.

33
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,270
No, you really did.

34
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,050
I told you I didn't.

35
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:58,090
But...

36
00:03:58,620 --> 00:03:59,620
Look.

37
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,060
Ah...

38
00:04:01,810 --> 00:04:03,130
Are you sure you're okay?

39
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:05,140
You looked totally spaced out just now.

40
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:07,060
Just now... well...

41
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,680
I was just thinking about work.

42
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,040
I got a little distracted.

43
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:13,609
Hey, isn't this Kiritani-san's business
card from the Secretarial department?

44
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:14,970
Why do you have this?

45
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:16,840
None of your business.

46
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:20,180
Speaking of which,

47
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:22,310
it just so happens that today,

48
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,810
I'm going out drinking with
the Secretarial department.

49
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:27,010
Are you free tonight, Shido-san?

50
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:30,290
One of the seniors had to
cancel at the last minute.

51
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:31,830
So I'm just a seat filler?

52
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,960
Yeah, pretty much.

53
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:39,210
But,

54
00:04:39,330 --> 00:04:41,740
Kiritani-san might be there too.

55
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,070
If you're interested in her,
you should definitely come.

56
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,640
Ah, but

57
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:49,999
someone else is organizing the girls' side,

58
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,476
so I'm not exactly sure who's showing up.

59
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,100
(Secretarial department Kiritani Yuka)

60
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:55,310
Ah...

61
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:58,570
- Sorry, I'll just ask someone else...
- I'll go.

62
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,200
Huh?

63
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:03,570
I said, I'll go.

64
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,020
Really?

65
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,750
Thank you!

66
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,159
Nice to meet you all.

67
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,810
Okay, and the last one.

68
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,479
I'm Kashimura Akari. Even though
I'm in the Secretarial department,

69
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:24,409
I'm currently just handling small tasks
like pouring tea and making copies.

70
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:25,439
I'll do my best to learn,

71
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,940
and I hope to stand on my own
two feet soon. Nice to meet you.

72
00:05:29,810 --> 00:05:30,810
Well then, everyone,

73
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:33,559
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

74
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,816
As expected of the Secretarial
department, you all look so glamorous.

75
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,349
By the way, I didn't expect
you to actually show up.

76
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:38,170
You really surprised me.

77
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:38,960
Seriously.

78
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,180
Who invited you?

79
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:40,770
I did.

80
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:41,770
Good job!

81
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,686
Actually, I've always wanted to join,

82
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:45,270
but I just never had the chance before.

83
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:46,839
It's the same for our Kiritani.

84
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,459
I told her, "You should come
to these things once in a while."

85
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:49,380
I practically had to drag her out here.

86
00:05:49,381 --> 00:05:51,600
I was surprised to see
Kiritani-san here too.

87
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,129
Good job to you too, Matsushita-san.

88
00:05:53,130 --> 00:05:54,170
Thanks for the compliment.

89
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:54,950
Oh, it was nothing.

90
00:05:54,951 --> 00:05:58,830
Well, I just felt like commuting between
home and work every day wasn't great for me.

91
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,010
So I gathered my courage and came.

92
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,700
Then we definitely need to
get all the juicy details today.

93
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,000
What details?

94
00:06:05,001 --> 00:06:06,189
All sorts of things, of course.

95
00:06:06,213 --> 00:06:08,281
Hey, what exactly are
you trying to find out...

96
00:06:10,890 --> 00:06:12,419
Sorry to keep you waiting.

97
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:14,710
- Here's the prosciutto pizza. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

98
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:17,260
Um, Kiritani-san.

99
00:06:17,570 --> 00:06:18,879
Even though I got your business card,

100
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,626
I'm really sorry I haven't
reached out to you.

101
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,960
Not at all, I know you're busy.

102
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:27,240
But to be honest, I was hesitating
all day about whether to come.

103
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:29,389
But I'm so glad I did when I
saw you were here, Shido-san.

104
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,390
You're too kind.

105
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:32,900
Also...

106
00:06:33,020 --> 00:06:37,230
I've always wanted a chance
to have a proper chat with you.

107
00:06:37,590 --> 00:06:38,590
Really?

108
00:06:39,252 --> 00:06:39,700
Yes.

109
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:42,860
You seem so gentle, Shido-san,

110
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:44,470
and you're so capable at work.

111
00:06:44,690 --> 00:06:48,090
You're basically the embodiment
of every woman's ideal type.

112
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,760
You're quite the smooth talker.

113
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:51,990
Maybe we should poach
you for the sales department?

114
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,060
I'm not just flattering you.

115
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:55,550
Is that true?

116
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,520
If so, then I'm flattered.

117
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,060
Do you really mean that?

118
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,400
Of course. Being praised
by you, Kiritani-san,

119
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,350
what guy wouldn't be happy?

120
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:06,510
Wow, you're such a charmer.

121
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,530
I am a top-tier salesman, after all.

122
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,349
Um, Shido-san.

123
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:17,830
You usually have a massive workload, right?

124
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,620
Not at all.

125
00:07:19,813 --> 00:07:20,813
I'm just like the rest of them.

126
00:07:21,061 --> 00:07:22,710
No, no.

127
00:07:22,930 --> 00:07:24,610
Wait, how did you know?

128
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:27,646
Don't underestimate the Secretarial
department's intelligence network.

129
00:07:27,670 --> 00:07:30,069
Because when I look at the monthly reports,

130
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:32,960
you're always juggling
several projects at once.

131
00:07:32,980 --> 00:07:34,796
And you manage to pull
them all off flawlessly.

132
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:35,820
Exactly.

133
00:07:35,821 --> 00:07:37,069
This guy isn't even human.

134
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:38,520
I am human.

135
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:44,970
So I couldn't help but worry a little.

136
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:47,790
I was wondering if you were
getting enough rest and relaxation...

137
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,240
You've never been good
at relaxing, even back then.

138
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:58,940
Ah.

139
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:01,050
Sleeping so soundly.

140
00:08:02,295 --> 00:08:03,955
No, I do get plenty of rest.

141
00:08:03,980 --> 00:08:05,680
I don't work once I get home.

142
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:07,700
I see.

143
00:08:07,910 --> 00:08:09,410
That's a relief.

144
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:13,059
I didn't expect you to
worry about me so much.

145
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:16,590
Yeah, I worried on my own,
and now I'm relieved on my own.

146
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,370
Hey, Kiritani-san, worry about me too!

147
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:23,809
- No way, don't joke around like that.
- Are you drunk already?

148
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:25,340
I'm not drunk.

149
00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:28,630
- I'm perfectly fine.
- Could I get a glass of water, please?

150
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:31,460
Minamide-san.

151
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,850
Are you okay?

152
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,026
You've had way too much to drink.

153
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:37,509
- I'm fine~
- How does look like you're fine?

154
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:39,689
Yotsuya-san is that
famous Yotsuya-san, right?

155
00:08:39,690 --> 00:08:42,700
Yeah, he and Shido-san
went to high school together.

156
00:08:42,830 --> 00:08:44,739
Even though neither of you are locals,

157
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:46,206
it's such a coincidence
that you ended up together.

158
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:47,430
What is that supposed to mean?

159
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:49,409
You two are quite famous.

160
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:51,956
Everyone says you're the rising
stars of Section 1 and Section 2.

161
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:55,430
Seriously, because this guy is
around, we're under so much pressure.

162
00:08:55,970 --> 00:08:57,259
Geez, are you okay?

163
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:59,820
- I'm fine...
- Go throw up.

164
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,160
Stop joking around.

165
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,590
I'm not that amazing.

166
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,880
Yotsuya...

167
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:11,040
That guy is truly capable.

168
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:12,490
Huh?

169
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,500
You...

170
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,500
Shido-san

171
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:20,690
actually praised Yotsuya-san...

172
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:23,680
Is it that rare?

173
00:09:24,370 --> 00:09:25,506
It's my first time hearing it...

174
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:26,580
Me too...

175
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:30,430
What the hell.

176
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:32,519
Do you two just go
around praising each other

177
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,380
behind each other's backs?

178
00:09:35,130 --> 00:09:36,230
What do you mean by that?

179
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,080
The other day at the office,

180
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:40,460
Yotsuya-san said the exact same thing.

181
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:45,030
Yotsuya-san,

182
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:46,730
you're still here?

183
00:09:46,930 --> 00:09:50,289
Oh, I was about to head out,

184
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:53,420
but an urgent matter came up, so
I've been dealing with it until now.

185
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,270
You're working hard too, Onishi.

186
00:09:58,710 --> 00:10:00,960
Because Shido-san works so hard,

187
00:10:01,430 --> 00:10:03,090
I want to help out a bit too.

188
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,080
Don't mind that guy.

189
00:10:05,990 --> 00:10:08,160
He's just foolishly
working himself to the bone.

190
00:10:09,770 --> 00:10:11,690
You don't need to drive
yourself crazy with him.

191
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,140
Aren't you the same, Yotsuya-san?

192
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,840
Your workload is about the
same as Shido-san's, right?

193
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,080
At the end of the day, I'm the same.

194
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:30,690
Because I want to be a man
worthy of being Shido's rival,

195
00:10:33,540 --> 00:10:35,140
that's why I can keep working this hard.

196
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:44,090
Wow, what the heck. That's so touching.

197
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,120
So you guys don't actually hate each other.

198
00:10:46,490 --> 00:10:49,610
You two are truly great
rivals. It's wonderful.

199
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:51,660
Yeah...

200
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:55,440
Ah, what's everyone drinking next?

201
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:02,130
Shido-san, do you have a favorite wine?

202
00:11:05,074 --> 00:11:08,447
(Red Wines: Cabernet
Sauvignon, Merlot, Pinot Noir...)

203
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:12,180
You like Cabernet, right?

204
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:15,860
Ah... I'll pass on the wine.

205
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:18,430
Hmm, want to switch back to beer then?

206
00:11:18,770 --> 00:11:20,390
Sure, I'll have a beer...

207
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,990
Alright, I win again.

208
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,860
Hey! What are you doing?!

209
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:31,280
Don't touch me.

210
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,380
Hey, Ryo!

211
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,490
Wait a sec.

212
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:45,040
He's taking this way too seriously.

213
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:47,950
Have you decided on your drinks?

214
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,720
I'll just have what
everyone else is having.

215
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,230
So it's the same after all.

216
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:59,730
- I'll go order then.
- Okay, thanks!

217
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:03,960
That's so good.

218
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,400
I'm down for another round.

219
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,210
What's everyone doing next?

220
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:11,520
- Ah, I have to get up early tomorrow...
- Seriously?

221
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,640
- I don't have to get up early tomorrow.
- Seriously?

222
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,089
What do you mean by "seriously"?

223
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:19,489
No, my "seriously" was
directed at Kiritani-san.

224
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:21,140
- Really?
- Yeah, yeah.

225
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,850
- I'll go.
- Awesome!

226
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:24,890
Shido.

227
00:12:25,010 --> 00:12:26,210
We're going to an after-party.

228
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:28,810
Ah, I think I'll head home.

229
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,140
Do you have to get up early tomorrow too?

230
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:33,600
No, I just drank a bit too much.

231
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:35,570
Are you okay?

232
00:12:36,370 --> 00:12:37,700
Yeah, I'm fine.

233
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,720
Thank you.

234
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:41,500
I'm planning to call it a night too.

235
00:12:41,650 --> 00:12:43,770
Perfect, let's walk to
the station together.

236
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:45,720
Sounds like a plan.

237
00:12:46,430 --> 00:12:47,430
Good work today.

238
00:12:47,450 --> 00:12:49,470
- Good work today.
- Well then, good work everyone.

239
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:51,500
Good work today.

240
00:12:56,230 --> 00:12:57,230
Are they together?

241
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,220
Nah, let's just go by ourselves.

242
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:00,350
Let's go, right now.

243
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:02,010
Alright, let's head out.

244
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,830
I had a lot of fun today.

245
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:11,290
It's really my first time
at a gathering like this.

246
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,396
The guys from our
department are pretty loud, huh?

247
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:14,420
No, not at all.

248
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:16,130
Everyone is really fun.

249
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:18,450
The time just flew by.

250
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:21,690
The people from the Secretarial
department are really fun too.

251
00:13:21,990 --> 00:13:23,730
I got to see a new side of everyone.

252
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:28,550
People from the Secretarial department might
give off the impression of being very capable.

253
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:30,490
But off the clock, they're just like that.

254
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,700
Kiritani-san, you're pretty
much the same as usual.

255
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:35,230
Yeah.

256
00:13:35,255 --> 00:13:36,775
I'm not used to letting my guard down.

257
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,120
We get along pretty well.

258
00:13:39,730 --> 00:13:41,310
I'm exactly the same.

259
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:45,070
What about when you're with Yotsuya-san?

260
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:46,880
Huh?

261
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,720
You guys have known each
other since high school, right?

262
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:51,489
I was wondering, if
you're with Yotsuya-san,

263
00:13:51,490 --> 00:13:53,020
do you ever let your guard down?

264
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,950
No, not at all.

265
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:13,080
I've never let my guard down around him.

266
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:15,340
We've always just been
competing with each other.

267
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,490
You're great rivals.

268
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:20,190
I wish I had a rival like that too.

269
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:24,080
Kiritani-san.

270
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:26,140
What's wrong?

271
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:30,770
Um...

272
00:14:34,070 --> 00:14:35,070
I...

273
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,640
Hmm?

274
00:14:43,780 --> 00:14:44,780
Shido-san.

275
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:49,900
Oh my.

276
00:14:51,350 --> 00:14:52,350
This.

277
00:14:52,351 --> 00:14:54,090
Looks like you left this at the restaurant.

278
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,090
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

279
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:59,030
- Well then, see you tomorrow.
- See you tomorrow.

280
00:15:08,660 --> 00:15:09,660
Shido-san.

281
00:15:14,770 --> 00:15:17,720
I'm taking the bus.

282
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,750
Ah...

283
00:15:20,890 --> 00:15:23,160
I see, then I'll take the train.

284
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,980
Well then, goodbye.

285
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:36,550
Okay, goodbye.

286
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,099
(Yotsuya Ryo)

287
00:15:56,100 --> 00:16:02,900
(Block this caller)

288
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:10,660
Zen, can you hear me?

289
00:16:12,690 --> 00:16:13,690
Zen?

290
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,240
Ugh!

291
00:16:19,110 --> 00:16:20,110
Um...

292
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:21,810
What's wrong?

293
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:24,030
Ah, nothing.

294
00:16:24,660 --> 00:16:26,550
I was just at a place called Break

295
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,216
drinking with the people from
the Secretarial department.

296
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,240
Oh...

297
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,910
Ah, I know that place.

298
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,320
The food is pretty good, right?

299
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:35,190
Yeah.

300
00:16:36,220 --> 00:16:37,610
Was Kiritani-san there too?

301
00:16:39,310 --> 00:16:40,310
Yeah, she was.

302
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:42,540
I see.

303
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:43,910
So,

304
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,250
what's this call about?

305
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:46,620
Huh?

306
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Ah...

307
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:49,580
No, um...

308
00:16:50,266 --> 00:16:51,952
The people from the
Secretarial department said

309
00:16:51,990 --> 00:16:53,360
they want to grab a meal with you.

310
00:16:54,010 --> 00:16:55,010
Huh?

311
00:16:56,110 --> 00:16:57,310
Just for that?

312
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,720
Yeah.

313
00:16:58,970 --> 00:16:59,970
That's right.

314
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,520
I'm not going.

315
00:17:01,930 --> 00:17:02,930
Not interested.

316
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,300
Say something at least.

317
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:12,150
Ah, nothing in particular.

318
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,240
No, um...

319
00:17:14,150 --> 00:17:15,580
Ah, the T-shirt.

320
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:16,950
T-shirt?

321
00:17:18,010 --> 00:17:19,336
The one I borrowed from you last time.

322
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:20,610
Oh.

323
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:23,020
I want to return it.

324
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,820
Come get it now.

325
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,200
Huh?

326
00:17:26,210 --> 00:17:27,210
Why?

327
00:17:27,350 --> 00:17:28,350
What do you mean, why?

328
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,560
Because it's a pain to take it back home.

329
00:17:30,610 --> 00:17:31,726
What does that have to do with me?

330
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:33,210
Do whatever you want with it.

331
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,690
Hey... wait...

332
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:42,110
What the hell am I doing?

333
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:34,381
Zen!

334
00:18:44,420 --> 00:18:45,420
Ryo?!

335
00:18:49,410 --> 00:18:50,610
The T-shirt.

336
00:18:51,370 --> 00:18:52,890
You don't even have it on you, do you?

337
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,390
You almost never call me on your own.

338
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:01,510
Ah.

339
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:03,430
You're drunk, aren't you?

340
00:19:06,170 --> 00:19:08,050
Don't tell me you missed me?

341
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:09,820
As if.

342
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,970
I just thought I brought it with me.

343
00:19:12,313 --> 00:19:13,313
Whatever.

344
00:19:13,830 --> 00:19:15,950
It doesn't matter when
you return that kind of thing.

345
00:19:17,850 --> 00:19:19,020
Since I'm already here,

346
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:22,583
I'll take a walk with you
to help you sober up.

347
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:26,689
I didn't bring the
T-shirt, so just go home.

348
00:19:26,690 --> 00:19:28,460
Hey, are you a monster?

349
00:19:29,490 --> 00:19:31,200
You're the one who called me here.

350
00:19:33,310 --> 00:19:34,630
I'm not going back.

351
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:38,310
Because I want to hang
out with you a little longer.

352
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:40,380
Let's go.

353
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,480
I see.

354
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,480
Hey.

355
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,940
Have you ever been inside that building?

356
00:21:33,670 --> 00:21:34,670
Never.

357
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:38,340
I heard there are a lot of
interesting shops inside.

358
00:21:39,930 --> 00:21:41,570
Let's go check it out together next time.

359
00:21:41,770 --> 00:21:42,870
As a date?

360
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,120
What do you mean, a date?

361
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:45,230
How boring.

362
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:47,700
You're always like this.

363
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:49,830
You always forget about our "competition."

364
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:52,090
I'm not free enough to
go on a date with you.

365
00:21:55,430 --> 00:21:59,510
I heard there's a braised pork
rice place you like there too.

366
00:22:00,010 --> 00:22:01,010
Huh?

367
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:03,990
I've never told anyone
I like braised pork rice.

368
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,859
When I took you to eat it before,

369
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,710
weren't you really enjoying it?

370
00:22:10,210 --> 00:22:11,730
You even remember something like that?

371
00:22:13,310 --> 00:22:15,070
You're terrifyingly observant.

372
00:22:16,510 --> 00:22:18,070
I've had my eyes on you the whole time.

373
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,880
I can't stand you.

374
00:22:22,310 --> 00:22:26,530
Then next time I win, you're treating me.

375
00:22:26,830 --> 00:22:27,830
Eh.

376
00:22:27,940 --> 00:22:29,550
You mean our competition at work?

377
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:31,620
Duh.

378
00:22:32,023 --> 00:22:34,869
Braised pork rice is way too cheap
of a reward for that competition.

379
00:22:34,870 --> 00:22:37,140
Why? Braised pork rice is delicious.

380
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:38,860
I mean, it is delicious, but...

381
00:22:41,470 --> 00:22:43,430
Well, you have a point.

382
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,880
Hey.

383
00:22:51,010 --> 00:22:52,010
Zen.

384
00:22:52,420 --> 00:22:53,420
Hmm?

385
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:57,490
After this competition is settled,

386
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:03,790
what... will happen to us?

387
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:08,720
Who knows...

388
00:23:12,470 --> 00:23:13,670
When that time comes...

389
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:16,430
we probably won't be able
to be friends anymore, right?

390
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,830
Hey, Zen...

391
00:23:32,970 --> 00:23:33,970
What is it?

392
00:23:37,550 --> 00:23:39,140
Maybe we should just call it off.

393
00:23:40,430 --> 00:23:41,540
This kind of competition.

394
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,400
(Next Episode Preview)

395
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:02,686
(Episode 5: I Really Don't Get It!)
Shido-san?!

396
00:25:02,710 --> 00:25:03,710
Sorry.

397
00:25:05,790 --> 00:25:06,850
Ah, Shido-san.

398
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,109
Just watching you makes me
feel like you're way too busy.

399
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:11,119
A stellar subordinate is truly dazzling.

400
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:12,680
You're really not honest with yourself.

